  "markup": "\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E1. Purpose \u0026amp; Scope\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003EThe Flexible Paid Time Off (FPTO) program provides eligible full-time employees the ability to take paid time off for vacation, personal business, illness, or other needs without a fixed annual accrual, subject to advance approval and business needs. This policy applies to all U.S.-based exempt employees unless otherwise specified by employment agreements, collective bargaining agreements, or applicable law.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E2. Guiding Principles\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EFPTO is intended to promote work-life balance while ensuring business continuity.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ERequests must be \u003Cstrong\u003Eplanned, documented, and approved\u003C/strong\u003E in advance, except in cases of illness or emergency.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EUse of FPTO must be consistent with performance expectations, role responsibilities, and coverage requirements.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E3. Eligibility\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l8 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EAvailable to full-time, salaried exempt employees after \u003Cstrong\u003E60 days\u003C/strong\u003E of employment.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l8 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EEmployees on a \u003Cstrong\u003EPerformance Improvement Plan (PIP)\u003C/strong\u003E require director-level approval for extended FPTO.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l8 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ETemporary, part-time, or hourly employees are not eligible unless explicitly approved by the People \u0026amp; Culture team.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E4. Request \u0026amp; Approval Process\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubmission:\u003C/strong\u003E All FPTO must be submitted in Replicon for manager review.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApproval Timeframe\u003C/strong\u003E: Managers will approve or deny requests within 3 business days.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApproval Criteria\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003EMinimum coverage requirements\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003EImpact on critical deadlines or deliverables\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003ENumber of overlapping approvals for the same period\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETie-Breaker Rule\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003EEarliest submission date\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003EBusiness criticality of employee\u2019s role during the requested time\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003EYTD PTO taken (priority given to those who have taken less)\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlackout Periods\u003C/strong\u003E: Certain dates (e.g., quarter-end, major releases) may be designated as blackout periods with \u003Cstrong\u003E30 days\u2019 notice\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E5. Planned vs. Extended vs. Unplanned FPTO\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlanned FPTO\u003C/strong\u003E: Request submitted \u22655 business days in advance.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtended FPTO\u003C/strong\u003E: Absence of 10\u002B consecutive business days requires \u226530 days\u2019 notice and a documented Coverage Plan.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnplanned FPTO\u003C/strong\u003E: Same-day notification permitted for illness or emergency. A pattern of 3\u002B unplanned non-medical absences in 60 days may result in performance or attendance review.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E6. Coverage Requirements\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003EFor absences over 5 consecutive business days, employees must attach a Coverage Plan to their request including:\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EDeliverable owners for all active work\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EOn-call contact information\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ELink to current status documentation\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l7 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ECommunication plan for clients or partners (if applicable)\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E7. FPTO in Connection with Other Leave Types\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l6 level1 lfo6; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECap:\u003C/strong\u003E When combined with another approved leave type (e.g., STD, parental leave), FPTO use is limited to 15 business days per leave event.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l6 level1 lfo6; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeave Event Definition\u003C/strong\u003E: A single continuous absence for the same reason, or related absences separated by \u003Cstrong\u003E\u226414 calendar days\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l6 level1 lfo6; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWaiting Periods\u003C/strong\u003E: FPTO may be used to bridge STD/LTD elimination periods (typically \u003Cstrong\u003E7\u201314 days\u003C/strong\u003E for STD; \u003Cstrong\u003E90\u002B days\u003C/strong\u003E for LTD).\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l6 level1 lfo6; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupplementation:\u003C/strong\u003E FPTO may be used to supplement disability pay up to \u003Cstrong\u003E100% of base pay\u003C/strong\u003E during the first 15 business days.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l6 level1 lfo6; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedical Release\u003C/strong\u003E: FPTO may not be used to extend paid time after medical clearance without standard FPTO approval.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E8. Sick Leave Compliance\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003EIn jurisdictions with statutory paid sick leave, the Company will track and administer sick leave in compliance with applicable law. FPTO may satisfy or supplement statutory entitlements.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E9. Holidays \u0026amp; High-Demand Dates\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003EFor PTO requests adjacent to Company holidays, managers may implement a rotation system to ensure fair distribution of high-demand dates.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E10. Notice Periods \u0026amp; Resignations\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003EDuring a resignation notice period:\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l0 level1 lfo7; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EPreviously approved FPTO may be honored.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l0 level1 lfo7; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ENew FPTO requests may be limited to 5 business days unless executive approved.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E11. Misuse \u0026amp; Consequences\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExamples of misuse include but are not limited to:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l4 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EProviding false or misleading reasons for absences\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l4 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ETraveling or engaging in other non-approved activities after denial of a request\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l4 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003ERepeated failure to log PTO usage in Replicon\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l4 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EWorking a secondary job during FPTO without disclosure and approval\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsequences:\u003C/strong\u003E Misuse may result in denial of future requests, written warning, or other corrective action up to and including termination.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E12. Manager Accountability \u0026amp; Appeals\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022margin-top: 0in;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l5 level1 lfo9; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EManagers must apply this policy consistently.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l5 level1 lfo9; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EEmployees may appeal a denial to the People \u0026amp; Culture team if they believe standards were not applied fairly.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-list: l5 level1 lfo9; tab-stops: list .5in;\u0022\u003EThe People \u0026amp; Culture team will audit FPTO usage and approvals quarterly to ensure equity and compliance.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E13. Company Rights\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003EThe Company reserves the right to amend, modify, or terminate this policy at any time, consistent with applicable law.\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
